            <ab>
               <lb type="inline" n="30v1_col2"/>
               <date type="cyclical">
                  <anchor type="date"/>
                  <seg type="date-y" subtype="v-mk"> ceya varuṣa</seg>
                  <seg type="date-sm" subtype="v-mk">paṅkuṉi <g facs="#m">m°</g></seg>
                  <seg type="date-md" subtype="v-mk"><num type="digit-o">14</num>
                     <supplied reason="illegible"><g facs="#d2">D2</g></supplied></seg>
               </date>
               <anchor type="scribe"/>
               <placeName>tayalkuṇāmpaṭṭaṇam</placeName>
               <persName role="grandFather">malaimaruntaiyar</persName> peraṉ 
               <anchor type="scribe"/>
               <seg type="pers"
                  subtype="scribe"><persName role="scribe">arumaruntaiyar</persName></seg> -
                  <placeName>kūṭalūrile</placeName>
               <persName role="guru">namacivāya<lb type="3" n="30v2_col2"/>ceṭṭiyār</persName>
               vīṭṭile paḷḷikkūṭam collukuṟa potu 
               <anchor type="copFor"/>
               <seg type="copFor-end" subtype="eḻuti-muṟṟ"
                  >eḻutiṉa 
                  <anchor type="item"/>
                  <seg type="copItem" subtype="title">pāṭṭiyal</seg> 
                  muṟṟum</seg> &#xBF3;
            </ab>
         </div>
         <div type="traslation">
            <head>Translation</head>
            <p>Year of Ceya, month of Paṅkuṉi, 14th [day] – the Pāṭṭiyal, which Arumaruntaiyar
               grandson of Malaimaruntaiyar of Tayalkuṇāmpaṭṭaṇam copied when Namacivāyaceṭṭiyār in
               Kūṭalūr taught (paḷḷikkūṭam collukuṟa) at [his] house, was completed.</p>
         </div>
